<P><H1 align=center>   COST MODELLING MENU – CM010</H1>
<H1 align=center>(pre-agreement in principle)</H1>
<P align=center></P>
<P align=center><H3>Create: </H3>clicking on the ‘Create Quote’ button on 
the right hand side of the screen causes the other buttons and fields in the 
screen to become active, so a quote can be created.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Maximum borrowing: </H3>this is at the top left hand 
side of the Cost Modelling Menu, clicking on this leads to <A HREF="HELP+CM055.asp">CM055</A> – this box 
displays a list of lenders and the maximum amount that the applicant can borrow 
according to their particular <A HREF="HELP_MortgageTerms.asp#income multiples">income multiples</A>.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Affordability: </H3>this is not available until further 
details have been entered (Agreement In Principle section) and the application 
assessed overall
<P></P>
<P><H3>To create quote: </H3>once the ‘Create Quote’ button 
has been clicked, the four product boxes on the left hand side are enabled and 
can be used to create quotes.
<P></P>
<P>         To create a mortgage 
quote, click on ‘Mortgage’. This leads to the <A HREF="HELP_CM100.asp">Loan Composition box (CM100)</A>.</P>
<P><STRONG>Once the Loan Composition box has been 
completed…</STRONG>        </P>
<P><H3>Buildings and Contents: </H3>clicking on this button on 
the left of the screen leads to <A HREF="HELP_CM020.asp">Buildings and Contents Details – CM020</A>. Once the 
Buildings and Contents Details screen has been completed and a quote calculated, 
this quote will appear in the box to the right of the ‘Buildings and Contents’ 
box.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Payment Protection: </H3>clicking on this button to the 
left of the screen leads to <A HREF="HELP_CM040.asp">Payment Protection Details – CM040</A>. Once the Payment 
Protection Details screen has been completed and a quote calculated, this quote 
will appear in the box to the right of the ‘Payment Protection’ box.
<P></P>
<P><U>Note:</U> if the applicant does not require Life Assurance, Buildings and 
Contents insurance or Payment Protection quotes, click on the box where the tick 
appears to the right of the main boxes, and a cross will appear indicating that 
this cover is not required.</P>
<P><H3>Calculate: </H3>when all details for the different 
components required have been completed (eg. Buildings and Contents, Payment 
Protection), click ‘Calculate’ and the total monthly cost for all components 
together will be calculated.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Quote Summary: </H3>clicking on the ‘Quote Summary’ 
button leads to <A HREF="HELP_CM060.asp">‘Quotation Summary’ – CM060</A>.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Stored Quotes: </H3>this leads to the <A HREF="HELP_CM065.asp">‘Stored Quotes’ 
screen (CM065)</A>.
<P></P>
<P><U>Note:</U> if another quote is required, select ‘Create Quote’ and follow the 
process again.</P>
<P>Clicking on ‘<STRONG>OK</STRONG>  ’ leads to the <A HREF="HELP_MN060.asp">Application Menu – MN060.</A></P>
<P>After Quick Quote, click on Agreement In Principle to proceed with the 
application. </P>

